review_blob: Incredibly complex beer. Due to the great equilbrium the alcohol (18.2%) is well hidden, allowing all the great and variegated flavours to happily invade your mouth. The beer is pitch dark and oily with low carbonation and a nut colored foam. In my opinion its a great conversation beer to be shared with friends after dinner.
Aroma and taste grave nothing to do with bock style. Its more similar to an IPA, but the bitterness its not balanced.
